May 18 2007 	Good location and value	Booked the hotel using lastminute dot com for 5 days between 12-17 May 2007.Probably the cheapest you can get for this part of town and it is in a more favourable than Deira, particulalry if you are likely to spendmore time in the Jumerirah beach resorts.A bus service collects from the airport hourly. However, I did not use it because a friend picked me up. It is worthwhile using because taxi journeys from the airport carry a special surcharge (20Dhs = £3). Journey time is about 10-15 minutes depending on traffic.Nice clean lobby area at the hotel with sofas and coffee tables for loafing around. Three internet terminals are available but not many people use it, probably because of the cost (was 24Dhs=£3.50 for 20 minutes or 72Dhs=£10 for 1 hour). Not sure what the price was for wireless.Room was clean though starting to get a bit scuffy. Shower leaked a bit but it wasn't much of a problem. Air conditioning very effective.The only disappointments were the lack of tea/coffee making facilities and the lack of English TV channels (a news channel sould have been nice).There's a small bar which is fairly busy and open 24-7. I only used it once and the prices seemed reasonable. Snacks are ordered here (sandwiches/fries etc). The Italian restaurant next door closes at midnight and I'm told it is reasonably good. A cafe is located a short walk inside the adjacnt convention centre and serves coffees and pre-prepared sandwiches and cakes etc..There's a small shop with post cards, maps, books, magazines. I bought a map there which was quite expensive.Breakfast in the hotel is buffet style and nothing spectacular. A choice of three cereals (cornflakes, museli or all bran), selection of yoghurts, fresh fruit salad, croissants, white and brown bread toast, fresh orange and apple juice, tea and coffee, cold meats and cheeses....The cooked breakfast didn't look that appetising and consisted of potato cakes/hash browns, beef bacon, sausages, beans and scrambled or fryed egg. The sausages looked like the economy ones out of Asda (Wall Mart)!!! Overall I was fairly happy with it and all the cutlery was clean. Coffee tasted quite nice too..The Novotel is a 5 minute walk through the exibition centre and I'm told you can use their facilities at cost. Taxis are very frequent and it costs an average of 21Dhs=£3 to get to most of the large shopping centres. There are several free bus services but the're not always that frequent so I took taxis for convenience, particulalry when returning to the hotel. Note that a Taxi to Wild Wadi Water Park(next to Jumeira Beach Hotel) is around 35Dhs= £5.Overall I would recommend this Hotel to anyone who wants the guarrantee of a quiet hotel, close to all the major shopping centres but at a modest price.The only downside besides the ones already mentioned is that there are no local shops where you can pick up water, snacks, or drinks after midnight. You have to make do with the bar food and drinks which obviously are going to cost more.	
