Dec 3 2006 	Pleasantly Surprised by This One!	I arrived about 7.30am in the morning after a 14 hour flight from Australia and was informed that check-in was 2pm, but that they would do their best to get me in earlier. I was happy to accept this and expected to have to go out feeling rather the worse for wear. At approximately 8.30am I was informed I could take my room and I was able to have a good rest before hitting the sights. I was not charged extra and I was extremely grateful that they did this, although no doubt they were keen to remove the tired-looking bedraggled traveler reclining sleepily in their foyer! I found the staff exceptionally friendly, helpful and polite, except for one snooty one who thankfully I had very little to do with. I was however quite perplexed by the fact that they did not advertise anywhere that they offer a free coach service to a number of Dubai malls and the beach area. The cabs in Dubai are inexpensive, but still, it is more convenient to take a coach from your hotel rather than try and flag down a cab in the heat. The Ibis is not far – but still a decent cab ride – from the main attractions. The breakfast was excellent and I popped into the lovely Cubo bar for drinks and snacks one afternoon. The rooms are basic but very clean. I’ve definitely had smaller. As this hotel is at the lower cost end (but still expensive for Australians staying there) I think it offers excellent accommodation and a high quality of service. I stayed there for two nights, transiting to Morocco, but maybe if you are looking for something more comfortable (there is no ‘view’ to speak of and the basicness of the room might get to you after a while) you could go elsewhere but it would cost you an arm and a leg. I was a woman travelling alone and felt very safe and looked after here. The airport pick ups and dropoffs were very efficient also.	
