Jan 20 2006	Excellent value for money	We stayed at this hotel for three nights from 31st December. You shouldn't expect luxuries like a bath tub, hair dryer, minibar,... but all the amenities that you would reasonably expect given the room rate are provided with a touch of design above its class.Free shuttle buses to and from the airport, to the beach and to three shopping malls in different parts of Dubai also help to keep expenses under control (not bad, given the countless opportunities to spend lots of money in Dubai).The staff is very kind, either at the reception desk or at the restaurants. We do like good food and can unconditionally recommend their Cubo restaurant: we tried some other places mentioned in the guidebooks and found it offered far better value for money than most. But don't expect to have the most memorable meal of your lifetime there: maybe the 400 AED per person, not including service charge and taxes (no kidding!) Japanese steak at the Fairmont hotel, at a mere 5 minutes walking distance from the Ibis would be a better bet for such a purpose (we didn't try however).	
